We constructed mini-batches of size {{arxiv_2111_13611_FO0080||FO}}, used the Adam optimizer initialized with a constant learning rate of {{arxiv_2111_13611_FO0081||FO}}-{{arxiv_2111_13611_FO0082||FO}} and {{arxiv_2111_13611_FO0083||FO}}-{{arxiv_2111_13611_FO0084||FO}} epsilon value, and trained for {{arxiv_2111_13611_FO0085||FO}} epochs. Since our dataset is imbalanced, we monitored validation precision to save the best model, and report optimal F1-scores [Lipton2014OptimalTO] to compare results.